notes_display: The death of Queen Mary.  This medal has no inscriptions except for artist's initials.  Appears to be an after cast with legend effaced on the molds.  Obverse is a copy of the work of Jan Boskam.
issue_obverse_figure_description_s: Mary II in mantle fastened with jewel, tiara on top of head, pearls around hair, lovelock.
issue_reverse_figure_description_s: Britannia holding a reversed torch, sits in a mournful attitude, leans against monument decorated with medallion of MARIA REGINA.  On ground lies a shield, crown, and anchor.
